frameDefinitions: This frame contains words which name permanent fixed structures forming an enclosure and providing protection from the elements.

This is an abstract frame for durative activities, in which the Agent enters an ongoing state of the Activity, remains in this state for some Duration of Time, and leaves this state either by finishing or by stopping.
A Theme is held in captivity by an Agent or Cause.
An Artifact is deliberately made or modified by an intelligent entity to be put to a certain kind of Use.
An Developer develops a Product, in some cases for a Company.    ''
A Social_event occurs at which Attendees are present to conduct a social function or joint activity.
frameExamples: The baroque <t>church</t>, built in 1635, has a very rich interior
Twenty soldiers were in <t>captivity</t> for over a month before they were released
There are reports that Kim Il Sung asked China to share its nuclear weapons <t>technology</t>.
The <t>development</t> of a profitable product will be necessary for the company to stay afloat. INI
Sue threw a <t>party</t> for Bob's birthday.
listRoleDefinitions: The entity built by the <fen>Builder</fen> which has some <fen>Function</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Activity</fen> in which the  <fen>Agent</fen>  is engaged.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Activity</fen> occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Activity</fen> occurs.
The area within which the <fen>Theme</fen> is confined.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Theme</fen> is held captive.
This role identifies the general <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Theme</fen> is held captive.

This role identifies the entity or substance that is designed to have a particular <fen>Use</fen>. This can refer to physical artifacts, like a mug or computer monitor, or a digital artifact, such as a website or document.
The entity which is developed by the <fen>Developer</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Product</fen> is developed by the <fen>Developer</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Product</fen> is developed by the <fen>Developer</fen>.
<fen>Attendee</fen> is used for the people who come to the <fen>Social_event</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Social_event</fen> occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Social_event</fen> occurs.
